<!-- ============ ARTICLE ============ -->
<section class="sec" style="padding-top:40px">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="post-wrap post-body reveal">
<p>Partnering effectively with a video agency to drive sales starts with treating the agency as a strategic partner, not a vendor: align on goals during discovery, agree on a clear concept before filming, and stay involved through post-production so the final video matches both your brand and your business objectives. Brands that follow this kind of structured process consistently get content that performs, because every stage — from the first discovery call to final delivery — is built around a measurable outcome rather than just a finished video.</p>
<h2>The Power of Video in Modern Marketing</h2>
<p>Consumer behaviour has shifted decisively toward video: a recent study found that 72% of customers prefer to learn about a product or service through video, and video content can increase conversion rates by up to 80%. These numbers explain why brands increasingly turn to a <a href={p("services/brand-video")}>video agency</a> to craft marketing strategies that deliver measurable results.</p>
<h2>Why Brands Need a Professional Video Agency</h2>
<p>There's a significant gap between in-house content and professionally produced video. Consumers now expect high-quality visuals, compelling storytelling, and seamless delivery, and brands that fall short risk losing prospects to competitors who don't. Partnering with a professional agency ensures your video content is on-brand and strategically aligned with your business goals, whether you're launching a product, rebranding, or running a targeted campaign.</p>
<h2>What a Strong Agency Partnership Looks Like</h2>
<p>The most productive agency relationships follow a clear, repeatable process:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Discovery and Strategy:</strong> An in-depth session to define goals, audience, and messaging before any creative work begins.</li>
<li><strong>Concept Development:</strong> A tailored video concept outlining visual style, tone, and narrative.</li>
<li><strong>Production Planning and Filming:</strong> Location scouting, crewing, and professional filming with the right equipment for the brief.</li>
<li><strong>Post-Production and Delivery:</strong> Editing, motion graphics, sound design, and colour grading, with the final video optimised for each platform it will run on.</li>
</ol>
<h2>Increase Product Sales with Targeted Video Content</h2>
<p>Product videos remain one of the most effective ways to influence purchasing decisions — a 2023 Wyzowl report found that 89% of consumers have been convinced to buy a product after watching a video. Well-made <a href={p("services/product-video")}>product videos</a> don't just engage buyers directly; they also become reusable assets for sales teams and digital campaigns, bridging the gap between interest and purchase.</p>
<h2>Case Study: Increasing Engagement with Siemens Video Content</h2>
<p>A standout example of what a strong agency partnership can produce is Viven's collaboration with Siemens Switzerland on a series of <a href={p("services/employer-branding")}>employer branding</a> videos showcasing their company culture. Over five filming days, Viven produced 120+ videos and 100+ photos capturing authentic stories from within the company. The result was a 3x increase in website and social media traffic, along with significantly higher organic engagement — content that continues to play a role in Siemens' long-term brand strategy.</p>
<h2>Video Marketing That Drives ROI</h2>
<p>Producing great video content is only part of the equation; ensuring it reaches the right audience at the right time is where an agency's strategic guidance matters most. Aligning distribution with your broader marketing strategy is what turns a well-made video into a video that delivers a solid return on investment.</p>
<h2>Ready to Transform Your Sales Strategy?</h2>
<p>Curious what sets one agency partnership apart from another? Read more on <a href={p("blog/why-viven-is-the-video-agency-of-choice-for-b2b-brands")}>why B2B brands choose Viven as their video agency</a>. Or <a href={p("contact")}>contact Viven</a> directly to discuss how a structured agency partnership can help drive your sales and strengthen customer engagement.</p>
